@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About";
}

<div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-3">
    <h2 class="mb-0">About D&amp;D Manager</h2>
</div>

<p class="text-muted mb-4">Your friendly companion for keeping campaigns organized, characters tracked, and chaos (mostly) under control.</p>

<hr />

<div class="row g-4 mb-4">

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-header"><strong>What Is This Thing?</strong></div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>
                    D&amp;D Manager is a web app built to take the paperwork out of your tabletop sessions so you can
                    focus on the fun stuff, like arguing over whether the bard can fight the dragon.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-0">
                    It keeps all of your campaign info in one spot: characters, session notes, encounters, and
                    combat tracking. No more digging through a pile of index cards or squinting at a spreadsheet
                    that looks like it was designed by a chaotic neutral wizard.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-header"><strong>Who Is It For?</strong></div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>
                    Mostly Dungeon Masters, but honestly anyone at the table can benefit from having a clean
                    record of what happened three sessions ago when the party accidentally burned down the tavern.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-0">
                    If you run multiple campaigns (you overachiever), the app handles those too. Each campaign
                    gets its own little world of characters, logs, and encounters completely separate from the rest.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

<h4 class="mb-3">What You Can Do</h4>

<div class="row g-3 mb-4">

    <div class="col-sm-6 col-lg-3">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-header"><strong>Campaigns</strong></div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p class="small mb-0">
                    Create and manage campaigns, keep track of who the DM is, and store a description
                    so everyone remembers what the whole adventure is actually about.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-sm-6 col-lg-3">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-header"><strong>Characters</strong></div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p class="small mb-0">
                    Track every character in the party: their class, race, level, HP, and AC.
                    Great for when someone insists their fighter has more HP than they actually do.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-sm-6 col-lg-3">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-header"><strong>Session Logs</strong></div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p class="small mb-0">
                    Log each session with a title, date, and a summary of what went down.
                    You can also attach individual log entries for more granular notes
                    (or for calling out that one player who was on their phone the whole time).
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-sm-6 col-lg-3">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-header"><strong>Combat Tracker</strong></div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p class="small mb-0">
                    Add combatants with initiative, HP, and AC to keep fights moving.
                    Way better than trying to track everyone on a whiteboard while also narrating
                    a dragon monologue.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

<h4 class="mb-3">How It Works</h4>

<div class="card mb-4">
    <div class="card-body">
        <ol class="mb-0">
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Start a Campaign.</strong> Head to the Campaigns page and hit <em>New Campaign</em>. Give it a name, drop in the DM's name, and add a quick description if you want.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Add Characters.</strong> Inside your campaign, add the party members. Fill in their stats so you have a handy reference during play.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Log Your Sessions.</strong> After each session, create a session log with a summary. Add log entries for specific moments worth remembering.</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Run Encounters.</strong> Set up encounters and add combatants to keep initiative and HP organized during fights.</li>
            <li class="mb-0"><strong>Come Back Next Week.</strong> Everything is saved and waiting for you. Just pick up where you left off.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <div class="card-header"><strong>A Note on This Project</strong></div>
    <div class="card-body">
        <p class="mb-0">
            This app was built as a course project for CIS-293 Advanced Technologies at Southeast Tech.
            It uses ASP.NET Core MVC with Entity Framework Core and SQL Server on the backend,
            and Bootstrap 5 on the frontend. It is a work in progress, so if something breaks, well,
            the dice were just not in your favor today.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
